			<item>
				<title>Choosing a game name</title>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;Choosing a game name stopped being fun 500 iterations ago. The original name “Golden Cannon” did
not feel right for how the game has turned out. Here is my criteria for success:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Memorable and short&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Availability: App store, domain availability, avoids trademark violations&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The mood: Mysterious &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The location: Ocean and Ships&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The genre: Puzzles&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The core mechanic: Tilting &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The first 2 points seem to conflict for most ideas. With over a million apps in the iOS store alone, 
many memorable and short app names are taken. Here are a few amassed with the help of my brother Keir.&lt;/p&gt;

